      "module_id": "m1",
      "title": "Marketing Concepts and Environment",
      "topics": [
        {
          "topic_id": "t1",
          "title": "Core Marketing Concepts",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "estimated_time": "15 min",
          "prerequisites": [],
          "learning_outcomes": [
            "Understand what marketing is",
            "Differentiate needs, wants, and demand"
          ],
          "content": "## Core Marketing Concepts\nMarketing is the process of identifying, anticipating, and satisfying customer needs profitably.\n\n### Key Concepts\n- **Needs**: Basic human requirements\n- **Wants**: Needs shaped by culture\n- **Demand**: Wants backed by purchasing power\n\n### Exchange Process\nMarketing involves exchange where value is transferred between buyer and seller.\n\n### Value and Satisfaction\nCustomer satisfaction depends on perceived value versus expectations.\n\n### Example\nA customer buying a smartphone is not just buying a device but value like status, usability, and brand trust.",
          "examples": [
            "Buying a premium phone for brand value",
            "Choosing a local product for affordability"
          ],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Confusing wants with needs",
            "Ignoring customer perception of value"
          ],
          "qna": [
            {
              "q": "What is marketing?",
              "a": "It is the process of satisfying customer needs profitably."
            },
            { "q": "What is a need?", "a": "A basic human requirement." },
            {
              "q": "Difference between wants and demand?",
              "a": "Demand is wants backed by purchasing power."
            },
            {
              "q": "What is value?",
              "a": "Perceived benefit compared to cost."
            },
            {
              "q": "Why is satisfaction important?",
              "a": "It leads to customer retention."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic_id": "t2",
          "title": "Marketing Environment",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "estimated_time": "20 min",
          "prerequisites": ["t1"],
          "learning_outcomes": [
            "Understand internal and external factors affecting marketing",
            "Analyze macro and micro environment"
          ],
          "content": "## Marketing Environment\nMarketing environment includes all factors that influence marketing decisions.\n\n### Micro Environment\n- Customers\n- Competitors\n- Suppliers\n\n### Macro Environment\n- Political\n- Economic\n- Social\n- Technological (PEST)\n\n### Importance\nUnderstanding environment helps firms adapt strategies.",
          "examples": [
            "Economic recession affecting demand",
            "New technology disrupting markets"
          ],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Ignoring external factors",
            "Overestimating internal control"
          ],
          "qna": [
            {
              "q": "What is marketing environment?",
              "a": "Factors affecting marketing decisions."
            },
            {
              "q": "What is micro environment?",
              "a": "Internal and close external factors."
            },
            {
              "q": "What is macro environment?",
              "a": "Broad external forces like economy."
            },
            {
              "q": "What is PEST?",
              "a": "Political, Economic, Social, Technological."
            },
            { "q": "Why important?", "a": "Helps adapt to changes." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
