          "content": "## Consumer Decision Process\nConsumers go through stages before purchasing.\n\n### Stages\n1. Problem recognition\n2. Information search\n3. Evaluation of alternatives\n4. Purchase decision\n5. Post-purchase behavior\n\n### Importance\nHelps marketers influence decisions.",
          "examples": [
            "Comparing phones before buying",
            "Reading reviews before purchase"
          ],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Ignoring post-purchase stage",
            "Assuming rational decisions always"
          ],
          "qna": [
            { "q": "What is first stage?", "a": "Problem recognition." },
            {
              "q": "What is evaluation stage?",
              "a": "Comparing alternatives."
            },
            {
              "q": "Why post-purchase important?",
              "a": "Affects repeat buying."
            },
            {
              "q": "What influences decisions?",
              "a": "Social, psychological factors."
            },
            { "q": "Example?", "a": "Reading reviews before buying." }
          ]
        }
